description:
Draft Resource Management Plan and Environmental Impact Statement, published December 2012
Theme: ERMA.shp 
Description: Extensive Recreation Management Areas (ERMAs) are areas where recreation is planned and actively managed on an interdisplinary basis in concert with other resources and resource programs. 
This was developed as part of the BLM Grand Junction Field Office Resource Management Plan (RMP). This data describes the chapter 2 alternatives for Extensive Recreation Management Areas (ERMAs) and is in the draft stage. Data developed by Aaron Young, BLM GIS Specialist and Marcia Rickey, EMPSi GIS Specialist from January 2010 to October 2010. Data modified 8/17/2011 to reflect new policy guidance from WO. Data decisions made by Michelle Bailey and Chris Pipkin. Data modified by Douglas Diekman, BLM GIS specialist. Castle Rock boundary follows V2 road and S road, as per the BLM  DeBeque Recreation Coalition MOA.  

Vintage: 2011. 

Source: Data was derived from current Surface Land Ownership and ID team input

Capture Methodology: As stated above. 

Steward: Michelle Bailey, Recreation Planner (970) 244-3047

Attribute: See Entity Attribute for further details. 

Reliability: As per GJFO GIS data. 

Intended use: Data used in developing and displaying ERMAs areas in RMP revision. 

Quality Control: GJFO GIS staff. 

Projection: UTM zone 13, Datum NAD 1983

Agency Contact: Douglas Diekman, GIS Specialist 970-244-3087 

NO WARRANTY IS MADE BY THE BUREAU OF LAND MANAGEMENT FOR THE USE 
OF THE DATA FOR PURPOSES NOT INTENDED BY THE BUREAU.


ERMA for alternative RMP development, created by Michelle Bailey and Douglas Diekman starting 7/16/2009.
